caption: Mediocre pizza joint. (Pizza ordered: veggie pizza). Crust was actually very well made and had a really good taste. Plentiful toppings of fresh veggies included peppers, onion, mushrooms, and broccoli. Spinach was not fresh however (  bland taste and wet, soggy texture showed clear signs of either canned or box frozen spinach ). Peppers were cut WAY too huge which looks nice but made it difficult to take a normal bite and enjoy.  Cheese has a decent pull and was very good. I would have liked it to be a bit more crispy on the bottom. It was floppy and soggy to where the toppings almost wanted to fall off. Nothing a good hit in the skillet wouldn't fix, but... I'm ordering out so I don't have to make or fix pizza. Might be personal preference though. You may like a softer crust.  Honestly there is better pizza to be found in Brooklyn. If you're looking for some not-terrible pizza at an okay price, order away!  If you want a true,  NYC / BK pizza experience - there are better places.
